column5: Can anyone tell me how the fishing is in this area?  Thanks!

Ive fished the area for a long time and the fishing can be from okay to outstanding depending on where you fish. Ive had pretty good luck on Red Cedar for smallies and wallys but my fave lake in the area is Wicksteed. The whole lake is surrounded by crown land and theres only one boat launch and it can be tricky at times. The wally,bass and pike fishing on Wicksteed is just awesome. 2 summers ago I got a 9.5lb wally.
Holy crap that is far up north!  Tony
That 9 and a halfer is still swimmin too. Betcha He's ten and a half by now.
Ahhh...kinda like anything North of the 407 is "way up North?"
